+{"id":"bd-24","title":"Support ID space partitioning for parallel worker agents","description":"Enable external orchestrators (like AI worker swarms) to control issue ID assignment. Add --id flag to 'bd create' for explicit ID specification. Optionally support 'bd config set next_id N' to set the starting point for auto-increment. Storage layer already supports pre-assigned IDs (sqlite.go:52-71), just need CLI wiring. This keeps beads simple while letting orchestrators implement their own ID partitioning strategies to minimize merge conflicts. Complementary to bd-9's collision resolution.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2025-10-12T16:10:37.808226-07:00","updated_at":"2025-10-12T16:10:37.808226-07:00"}
